definition: to take out/to extract
to draw out/to pull out from in between/to remove part of the whole/(of certain plants) to sprout or bud/to whip or thrash

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc

sentences.english: Pull the top session of the dress out for the drapery effect both in the front and in the back;
sentences.chinese: 將裙子的前後壓在裏層的部分抽出，做出褶皺的效果。

sentences.english: Harry pulled his copy of Advanced Potion-Making out of his bag and looked up Felix Felicis.
sentences.chinese: 哈利從書包裏抽出《高級魔藥製作》，查找福靈劑。

sentences.english: Summer heat, has been out of bud and leaf stems.
sentences.chinese: 夏日炎炎，芽已抽出莖和葉。

sentences.english: And they have to put in a certain amount of work time, working at the Food Co-op .
sentences.chinese: 他們得抽出一部分時間去食品供銷社工作。

sentences.english: Janet pulled the page from her typewriter and looked nervously at her wrist-watch.
sentences.chinese: 簡尼特從她的打字機裏抽出紙，緊張地看了看手錶。

sentences.english: She withdrew her hand timidly form his arm.
sentences.chinese: 她怯怯地從他的胳膊中抽出手來。

sentences.english: Take a thread and weave a blanket, that’s what he used to say.
sentences.chinese: 抽出根線頭，織出條毯子，他經常這麼說的。

sentences.english: Even with the air pumped out the bulb, the tungsten filament slowly vaporizes.
sentences.chinese: 即使燈泡中的空氣被抽出，鎢絲也會慢慢地蒸發。

sentences.english: Thank you for taking the time in his busy schedule to read my job materials.
sentences.chinese: 感謝您在百忙之中抽出時間來閱讀我的求職材料。

sentences.english: I'm very appreciate your precious time to interview me.
sentences.chinese: 常感謝您能在百忙之中抽出時間來面試我。

sentences.english: As the water was unexpectedly hot, he jerked his hand out.
sentences.chinese: 沒想到水有這麼燙，他急忙將手抽出。

sentences.english: We still have two hours to spare.
sentences.chinese: 我們還可以抽出兩小時的時間。

sentences.english: I think there's a value in taking the time out.
sentences.chinese: 很有必要抽出一點時間。

sentences.english: The pump sucked water from the basement.
sentences.chinese: 水泵把地下室裏的水抽出來了。

sentences.english: For one week, go to sleep one hour earlier than usual.
sentences.chinese: 抽出一個禮拜，比平常早睡一個小時。

sentences.english: Also known as the pull and pray method.
sentences.chinese: 通常也被叫做“抽出來祈禱法”。
